dialogue.text:
Algorithm engineer for commercial implementation and maintenance of some projects 2021.07-present

1.AMT (Automatic Music Transcription) part: design, training, optimization, export of piano, guitar and other transcription models, as well as the update and maintenance of some existing cooperation protection, and finally commercialized it in the form of SDK, with a contract amount of hundreds of thousands of yuan;
2. Voice part
2.1. Voice cloning new timbre training, the entire pipeline from data processing to model export, new timbre as part of business cooperation;
2.2. Fine-tuning and delivery of tts and singing voice clones as part of commercial cooperation;
2.3. Voice conversion: Mainly ppg-based method, from data processing to model export, deployment and delivery, as a module of million-level contracts;
3. Music algorithm part
3.1. Waveform combination model: From the own music fragment library, select combinable waveform fragments through the trained model, deliver the finished product to the music group, and then provide it to partners;
3.2. Audio feature extraction model: train the model to extract audio features for downstream tasks such as similar song query, music style analysis, etc.;
3.3. Exploration of text and picture soundtracks and simple implementation attempts, and exploration of video soundtracks;
3.4. Video soundtrack comparison: This is a cooperative project. Based on audio fingerprints and audio vectors, the video soundtrack that matches the music library is found, and the partner performs further operations (such as rights protection);
3.5. Automatic music labeling: refine a music description model, then let LLM extract music-related tags, and realize automatic music labeling through post-processing, which can be used in business cooperation;
4.Others
4.1. Export the model within the group, explore the potential realization possibilities of the group’s existing technologies, track cutting-edge technologies, and explore the integration of new technologies with the company’s business;
4.2. AIGC, exploration of text2music, img2music, text2video; 
4.3. Some work related to large models, mainly in the application layer (mainly task adaptation, LLM as base + head/specific module), but also in some relatively small ones Do fine-tuning, adapter and other work on some models;
 4.4. Business promotion "agent": Based on the company's existing products, write a workflow, crawl relevant web pages online, find potential cooperative users based on LLM analysis, and then Let LLM write an email and send it to potential partners. Currently, there are several companies interested in cooperation;

Wanyin Recommendation System Algorithm Engineer 2020.05-2020.10

Participated in the recommendation system of the Wanyin APP that the company mainly promoted at the time.
1. u2u2i automated process deployment: Based on user behavior logs, and then based on user collaboration, we obtain each user’s recommendation list and dump it to online mysql; the data follows ods, dws and ads three layers, hive table cache is used in the middle, and scheduled workflow is implemented based on airflow;
2. Recommended system query service goes online: Agree with the backend to use grpc, register the service in consul, implement the grpc service according to specific needs and go online. The online process follows the order of three environments: dev, fat, and pro;
3. Similar song recall based on milvus uses musicnn to extract song feature vectors, and uses this to recall similar songs. Real-time recall is implemented through milvus as i2i, and the grpc service is online;
4. Duplicate song filtering: separate audio tracks, extract features from bgm, calculate the audio fingerprint for each song, and then recall a certain amount of "similar" songs based on milvus, the songs are then filtered through audio fingerprint matching, finally achieving second-level response and an accuracy rate of over 90%, and the grpc service is written and launched online;
5. Part of the work related to the vector database was published as a user case on the Zilliz official account (https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/5jL80Rm74gmf9v-Xrpw5Pw)

Controllable music generation algorithm engineer 2019.07-2021.07

Mainly symbolic music (focus on midi) is generated, and part of the output is converted into commercial cooperation.
1.Skyful music material generation: For a song's multi-tracks (piano, bass, guitar, etc.), build a library respectively. For a new song, find the most similar ones for each track except drums, and then use Vae interpolation, reorganized into a new song, after postprocessing, as one of the materials of Skyful app; 
2.Skyful material improvement: magic modification of musicvae, using drums and chord progression as conditions to generate bass, and then drums, chord progression, and bass generate pad , cascade is performed, this method as an alternative to the previous method which does not take into account inter-track coordination;
3. Pictures generate music exploration: Pictures and music data are aligned through emotional labels, both are trained with VAE, and the hidden information z in the middle is interacted based on flow, and finally a given picture, generate a piece of music that matches the "emotional atmosphere";
4. Controllable midi generation based on transformer: using NLP method and seq2seq architecture to accelerate model training and compression encoding, the speed is increased by about 3 times; to increase diversity, reference style tokens; for online display, explore model distillation , and finally the model was reduced to 1/7 of its original size under the premise of similar effects;
5. Improvements in controllable midi generation:
5.1. In terms of data: the multi-track merge logic of the data set is optimized to improve data quality;
5.2. Model: A new track mask is added to control the condition and target track conditions, and "prompt" the track to be generated by the model, making the model more controllable;
5.3. Training: Experiments related to model size, data size, and computing resources. When the card is insufficient, gradient accumulation is used to achieve the effect of large batch size;
5.4. Effect: Compared with before, the generated midi sound is richer and more audible. Some of the output has been used for commercialization.
6. Text-generated music exploration: There are a batch of music data sets with text labels (some professional descriptions). We use text models and music models to extract features, and then align them in the latent space, and finally achieved a given text description to generate a piece of music that roughly matches. Based on this, we also did some work of recalling similar songs and automatically marking songs. The effect is not very amazing

Professional skill

Proficient in using Python, can complete most engineering and research work, general C++, and have certain project experience;
Familiar with common data structures and algorithms, and familiar with basic operations of Linux systems;
Familiar with the basic operations of mysql, hive, and hadoop; have some experience in spark and k8s; 
familiar with the basic principles of common machine learning algorithms (LR, CRF, etc.) and common neural networks (RNN, LSTM, Transformer, etc.), and can independently solve them on specific problems Explore applications;

English level: CET-6, able to read English documents without any difficulty

Personal advantage

Love the Internet industry, love to delve into, dare to accept challenges, and are willing to try directions that the team has not been involved in; 
pay attention to industry trends, be full of curiosity and enthusiasm for new technologies, and have strong learning ability; 
Have good team awareness and teamwork spirit, work seriously and responsibly;

Work experience

Algorithm Engineer at Hangzhou EnjoyMusic Technology Co., Ltd. 2019.07-present

Controllable music generation, mainly symbolic music, with a small amount of waveform work, and part of the output is converted into commercial cooperation;
Recommendation system: offline u2i, i2i of the company’s music APP, and online i2i available initially;
Music algorithm: mainly some practical exploration of music/audio, and some of the work has commercial cooperation;
Voice: Voice conversion, from training to delivery cooperation, also doing some ASR, voice clone, TTS and singing work;
Commercial implementation and maintenance: technology realization and maintenance of some existing cooperation projects;
Some of AIGC's work related to large models is mainly at the application layer, and some of the work is used for personal use and converted into commercial cooperation;

